<center><span style="font-size: 30pt;">Cottagecore.</span><br>''One touch of nature makes the whole world kin.''






There stood a house of humble form and build
<br>Hemmed in by pet'ls of flowers and walls of bark.
<br>About this house no songbird called nor shrilled
<br>For solace amid nature was its mark. 

Of memory did the cottage partake
<br>To shift its form and please the wand'rer's eye;
<br>Their mother's mother's oven-warmèd bake,
<br>Their father's mother's biscuits, sweets, and pie. 

Beyond the cottage lies a lonely road, 
<br>About this road there lies a meadow wide,
<br>Around this field lie hills, unkempt, unmowed,
<br>And beyond this, only woodland lies outside.

So thank Wyatt for this refuge, his gift,
<br>In the core of this cottage, in this realm ashift. 

<small>''~ Anonymous, c. 1976''</small>

</center>













