== Description ==
'''Level 180''' is a level taking the form of an infinite expanse of greenery with humble "cottagecore" aesthetics. Upon first entering the level, a wanderer will find themself in a two-storey cottage with a thatched roof and a rural appearance, built of a substance analogous to concrete and surrounded by a low wooden fence — Grandma's house. Between fence and house, there is a small garden where flowers, such as roses and violets, bloom, as well as the occasional tree. The grass is always green and lush; the plants need no watering. 

Within Grandma's house, the wanderer will find things which remind them, in a kindly fashion, of their grandmother; bread, flowers, handmade quilts, unfinished knitting and apple pie are common objects to discover. While the general layout of the cottage always remains the same, there may be subtleties which alter between wanderers — the patterning on wallpaper, the scent of the place, the kind of flowers which blossom in the garden. There is always a kitchen, and it is always packed with nourishing foods and amenities. 

Even if a wanderer has never known their grandmother, or never loved their grandmother for any reason, the cottage will nonetheless still treat them with grandmotherly warmth. 

It is never nighttime in Level 180. While nobody has ever observed a sun, there does exist a point in the sky from which all light in the level derives, and this point seemingly bounces, to and fro, from horizon to horizon, instead of dipping beneath as does the sun of [[the Frontrooms]]. When this source is closest to either horizon, that is simultaneously the morning and the evening of the level; and when it is highest in the sky, that is the level's noontide. Compasses and radio equipment do not function in this level. 

{{Blurimage|file=Cottagecore hills.jpg|caption=The rolling hills.|align=left}}
Beyond the fence which surrounds the cottage, there is a lonely country Road which stretches on for miles in the midst of a large green meadow of flowers like daisies. It snakes through the endless countryside of Level 180, going nowhere, going everywhere, all at once; there are some who allege that trekking far enough across its gravelly length may lead one to the Grandma's house of another wanderer. This claim has not been proven, but perhaps the notion that one is truly not alone in the vast expanse of this world is a comforting one. And who knows? If it was not true before, [[Phenomenon 9|it may be true now]]. 

If one wanders far enough into the flat meadows and away from the lonely Road, they will eventually come to an endless set of hills, the home of many desolate wooden barns and lodges in which nobody lives. Even further still, one will come to the Forest, a woodland of thinly concentrated oaks and willows, which has been theorised to act as an encircling boundary to the entire level. Within the Forest, many natural features have been observed, including rivers, ponds, small lakes, boulders, and fungi such as mushrooms. But as for what lies beyond the Forest, it has never been ascertained. 

== Entities ==
Butterflies of many colours may be found fluttering all over Level 180, especially in the daisy fields around the Road and in the deeps of the Forest. They are friends and familiars of Wyatt; they never age, nor tire. 
<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-archangel">{{Blurimage|file=Angel looks to man.jpg|caption=Archangel Wyatt. Photograph taken by the [[Entity 1|Cameraman]].}}
=== Archangel Wyatt ===
'''Archangel Wyatt''' is an entity who assumes the form of an angel — a humanoid creature with wings peeking out from the top of his back. Wyatt manifests chiefly in stone statues scattered around the level, like sentinels overlooking a lonely, quaint land. These statues never speak nor move, but those wanderers who have looked into their eyes claim that there was something beyond lifeless stone in them. Many have called Wyatt the creator of Level 180, and they revere him. 

Wyatt's nature is entirely unknown, but if Christian tradition is to be believed, he may actually be an archangel sent by God to create a safe haven in the Backrooms and to act as a bridge between Heaven and Wake. His level's homely appearance, and its accents of greenery and nature, are representative of humility and refuge, a humble sanctuary amidst these satanic hells. Wyatt himself seems to have a connection to butterflies; they flock to his statues in fervent congregations, and sometimes he is depicted even with a crown of stone butterflies upon his head like a halo. 

"Wyatt's Blessing" refers to an anomalous phenomenon which seems to cause wanderers to become immune to damage, in any form, from the horrors of the Backrooms for a few months after exiting Level 180. It is the one detail which truly led some to believe the level is not simply a safe haven or a paradise, but a gift from God Himself. </div><div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-archangel">{{Blurimage|file=Angel looks to man.jpg|caption=<s>Arch</s>angel Wyatt. Photograph taken by the [[Entity 1|Cameraman]].}}
